[normal]Alan Clarke[bold]: From my recollection, we picked up quarter on quarter in the third quarter GDP, partly reversing the drop in the second quarter, so year on year, we are down 6.3%. Why have they been reducing investment? I guess the uncertainty of the last year, when plausibly someone could have left the 
[normal]Eurozone
