[normal]Alan Clarke[bold]: It is a further unwelcome headwind, but as a proportion of household disposable income, I worked the pay-outs out to be a drag of 0.25 to 0.5 of a percentage point on household disposal income, so wage inflation picking up from 1 to 2 would more than offset that, but it is cross your fingers and hope that wages pick up, because employment is going up.
[normal]&#xa0;
